# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Frontend dev/runtime config.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) to override per-machine defaults.
# Vite reads `.env*` at startup; restart the dev server after editing.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Where the SPA sends every `/api/*` call.
#
# DEFAULT (left empty): the SPA uses relative URLs. In `npm run dev`, that means
# Vite proxies `/api` → http://localhost:5099 (see vite.config.ts). Same-origin,
# no CORS preflight, OAuth callback works at /api/credentials/oauth/callback
# under the SPA's own port.
#
# DIRECT MODE (this var set to a full origin): every API call goes to that
# origin directly, skipping the Vite proxy. Useful when you want to:
#   - hit a backend running on a different host (LAN dev, remote tunnel)
#   - hit a local API that isn't on 5099 (custom port, container)
#   - debug CORS in dev with the same path the production deploy will use
#
# Requirements when you set this:
#   1. The backend's `Cors:AllowedOrigins` (appsettings) must list this SPA's
#      origin — http://localhost:5180 is added automatically in Development,
#      anything else needs an explicit entry.
#   2. The backend's `OAuth:CallbackUrl` must point at THIS SPA's origin too
#      (e.g. http://localhost:5180/api/credentials/oauth/callback), because
#      the OAuth popup messages back into the SPA window.
#
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5099
